00:00:20.880 --> 00:00:23.790 align:middle line:10%
>> The Lost Ark of the
Hebrews is today referred

00:00:23.790 --> 00:00:26.550 align:middle line:10%
to as the Lost Ark
of the Covenant.

00:00:26.550 --> 00:00:29.010 align:middle line:84%
Here's a very nice
picture of what

00:00:29.010 --> 00:00:33.480 align:middle line:84%
the Lost Ark of the Covenant
of the Hebrews looked like.

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:36.180 align:middle line:10%
But here, we have a picture of
the Ark of the Covenant carried

00:00:36.180 --> 00:00:38.350 align:middle line:10%
by the priest of Israel.

00:00:38.350 --> 00:00:42.330 align:middle line:10%
It's a large chest
with two angels sitting

00:00:42.330 --> 00:00:44.070 align:middle line:10%
on the top of the chest.

00:00:44.070 --> 00:00:45.990 align:middle line:84%
And incidentally,
the chest was said

00:00:45.990 --> 00:00:50.760 align:middle line:84%
to be so important and so holy
that one could not actually

00:00:50.760 --> 00:00:51.690 align:middle line:90%
touch it.

00:00:51.690 --> 00:00:54.460 align:middle line:84%
You would not want to
touch it, for you will die.

00:00:54.460 --> 00:00:59.550 align:middle line:84%
And so God said to put ring
eyes on the side of the chest

00:00:59.550 --> 00:01:01.950 align:middle line:84%
and put poles through
it so you could carry it

00:01:01.950 --> 00:01:03.700 align:middle line:90%
without touching it.

00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:05.489 align:middle line:84%
So that's interesting,
that this is

00:01:05.489 --> 00:01:08.550 align:middle line:84%
a general idea about what
the Ark of the Covenant

00:01:08.550 --> 00:01:11.660 align:middle line:90%
of the Hebrews looked like.

00:01:11.660 --> 00:01:16.670 align:middle line:84%
The Ark of the Covenant was a
symbolic connection between God

00:01:16.670 --> 00:01:19.370 align:middle line:84%
and the Hebrew people,
the things which

00:01:19.370 --> 00:01:21.500 align:middle line:84%
both God and the
Hebrew people held

00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:24.590 align:middle line:84%
to be so sacred to
their relationship.

00:01:24.590 --> 00:01:28.070 align:middle line:84%
So the idea was that both God
and the Hebrew people agreed

00:01:28.070 --> 00:01:30.110 align:middle line:84%
on certain things
were so important

00:01:30.110 --> 00:01:32.480 align:middle line:84%
that they would put
them into this chest,

00:01:32.480 --> 00:01:34.440 align:middle line:84%
and protect it and
keep it together.

00:01:34.440 --> 00:01:37.010 align:middle line:84%
And so it represented
God's connections

00:01:37.010 --> 00:01:41.450 align:middle line:84%
with the ancient Hebrew people,
the most important symbols.

00:01:41.450 --> 00:01:45.530 align:middle line:84%
We're told in the Book of
Revelation what the items were.

00:01:45.530 --> 00:01:48.410 align:middle line:84%
And we'll get into that
later, because it's actually

00:01:48.410 --> 00:01:52.390 align:middle line:84%
written in the Bible what was
in the Ark of the Covenant.

00:01:52.390 --> 00:01:54.460 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't used as
a weapon as such,

00:01:54.460 --> 00:01:57.560 align:middle line:84%
but we're told that it
was able to kill you.

00:01:57.560 --> 00:02:00.490 align:middle line:84%
It was able to strike you
dead if you touched it.

00:02:00.490 --> 00:02:03.700 align:middle line:84%
But I don't know if it was
actually used as a weapon.

00:02:03.700 --> 00:02:05.700 align:middle line:84%
But it was a
protection, supposedly,

00:02:05.700 --> 00:02:08.470 align:middle line:84%
that God put on that,
that if you touched it

00:02:08.470 --> 00:02:11.980 align:middle line:84%
without permission,
you could die.

00:02:11.980 --> 00:02:13.720 align:middle line:84%
Today, we have
pictures like this

00:02:13.720 --> 00:02:19.030 align:middle line:84%
showing the Israeli priests,
the ancient priests of Israel,

00:02:19.030 --> 00:02:23.930 align:middle line:84%
showing how much they adore
this magic and important Ark

00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:24.730 align:middle line:90%
of the Covenant.

00:02:24.730 --> 00:02:27.360 align:middle line:90%


00:02:27.360 --> 00:02:31.510 align:middle line:84%
Here's a picture of King
David bringing the Lost Ark

00:02:31.510 --> 00:02:34.120 align:middle line:90%
of the Covenant into Jerusalem.

00:02:34.120 --> 00:02:38.660 align:middle line:84%
And everyone not in the
procession is on their knees,

00:02:38.660 --> 00:02:42.220 align:middle line:84%
realizing that the Ark was
representing the very presence

00:02:42.220 --> 00:02:44.780 align:middle line:90%
of their God in their presence.

00:02:44.780 --> 00:02:49.954 align:middle line:84%
And these were very holy
symbols to the Jewish people.

00:02:49.954 --> 00:02:51.370 align:middle line:84%
There have been
many books written

00:02:51.370 --> 00:02:53.410 align:middle line:84%
about the Lost Ark
of the Covenant,

00:02:53.410 --> 00:02:57.820 align:middle line:84%
of course, and two books
in particular that deal

00:02:57.820 --> 00:03:00.250 align:middle line:90%
with the point I wish to make.

00:03:00.250 --> 00:03:03.340 align:middle line:10%
One is called "Lost
Secrets of the Sacred Ark."

00:03:03.340 --> 00:03:07.120 align:middle line:10%
And of course, there have been
a lot of lost secrets relating

00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:08.830 align:middle line:10%
to the Sacred Ark.

00:03:08.830 --> 00:03:13.720 align:middle line:10%
Sir Laurence Gardner in England,
which was Sir Laurence Gardner,

00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:15.190 align:middle line:10%
he had been knighted
by the Queen,

00:03:15.190 --> 00:03:18.550 align:middle line:10%
and he was an expert on
these arcane subjects

00:03:18.550 --> 00:03:20.680 align:middle line:10%
like the Ark of the Covenant.

00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:23.980 align:middle line:84%
And then there's another one
called "Secrets and Mysteries

00:03:23.980 --> 00:03:25.510 align:middle line:90%
of the Lost Ark."

00:03:25.510 --> 00:03:29.000 align:middle line:84%
So the reason why these two are
important to my conversation

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:30.970 align:middle line:84%
is because I want to
emphasize that there

00:03:30.970 --> 00:03:35.140 align:middle line:84%
were a lot of secrets
and mysteries in relation

00:03:35.140 --> 00:03:38.680 align:middle line:84%
to the Ark that maybe people
still don't know today.

00:03:38.680 --> 00:03:42.700 align:middle line:84%
So the most important
secret of all concerning

00:03:42.700 --> 00:03:46.180 align:middle line:84%
the Lost Ark of the
Hebrews is it was not

00:03:46.180 --> 00:03:48.280 align:middle line:90%
Hebrew at all to start with.

00:03:48.280 --> 00:03:51.400 align:middle line:84%
There was no Hebrew
Ark in history.

00:03:51.400 --> 00:03:54.910 align:middle line:84%
The whole idea of an Ark
of the Covenant, covenant

00:03:54.910 --> 00:03:58.270 align:middle line:84%
simply means contract,
and so the whole idea

00:03:58.270 --> 00:04:01.780 align:middle line:84%
the Ark of the Contract or
Covenant was not Hebrew at all,

00:04:01.780 --> 00:04:03.970 align:middle line:90%
it was Egyptian.

00:04:03.970 --> 00:04:06.980 align:middle line:84%
And so let me show you
what I'm talking about.

00:04:06.980 --> 00:04:10.960 align:middle line:10%
If you go to Bible dictionaries
and look up the word ark,

00:04:10.960 --> 00:04:13.900 align:middle line:10%
you will see that even the
Bible dictionaries tell you

00:04:13.900 --> 00:04:18.000 align:middle line:10%
that the very word ark
comes from the Egyptian.

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:21.790 align:middle line:10%
And then it shows you
a typical Egyptian ark.

00:04:21.790 --> 00:04:24.230 align:middle line:10%
And then if you go to
another Bible dictionary,

00:04:24.230 --> 00:04:29.290 align:middle line:10%
it talks about the Egyptian
ark, or the sacred chest.

00:04:29.290 --> 00:04:31.210 align:middle line:10%
And so now you
begin to see, when

00:04:31.210 --> 00:04:34.930 align:middle line:10%
you start doing the research on
the Lost Ark of the Covenant,

00:04:34.930 --> 00:04:38.020 align:middle line:10%
you begin to see that
a lot of pictures

00:04:38.020 --> 00:04:40.570 align:middle line:10%
have come out of the
ancient world showing you

00:04:40.570 --> 00:04:44.470 align:middle line:10%
that the Egyptians had
an ark, not the Hebrews.

00:04:44.470 --> 00:04:48.370 align:middle line:84%
And here is an Egyptian
ark and an Egyptian priest

00:04:48.370 --> 00:04:50.890 align:middle line:90%
in an Egyptian museum.

00:04:50.890 --> 00:04:53.830 align:middle line:84%
So my point in showing
you this is the fact

00:04:53.830 --> 00:04:57.730 align:middle line:84%
that the Lost Ark of the
Covenant was borrowed,

00:04:57.730 --> 00:05:00.950 align:middle line:84%
the idea was borrowed
from the Egyptians.

00:05:00.950 --> 00:05:03.580 align:middle line:10%
Here's an ancient
Egyptian priest

00:05:03.580 --> 00:05:08.950 align:middle line:10%
with a golden ark on an
ancient Egyptian wall

00:05:08.950 --> 00:05:12.340 align:middle line:10%
painting showing the priest
carrying the golden ark.

00:05:12.340 --> 00:05:17.220 align:middle line:10%
And this particular one
picture is on the Temple Ramses

00:05:17.220 --> 00:05:19.030 align:middle line:10%
at Abydos in Egypt.

00:05:19.030 --> 00:05:23.980 align:middle line:10%
And you will see there is the
Ark, the Ark of the Contract,

00:05:23.980 --> 00:05:25.570 align:middle line:10%
the Ark of the
Covenant, but you don't

00:05:25.570 --> 00:05:29.140 align:middle line:10%
see Hebrews priests carrying
it, you see Egyptians,

00:05:29.140 --> 00:05:32.400 align:middle line:10%
because it was an Egyptian
ark to start with.

00:05:32.400 --> 00:05:36.610 align:middle line:84%
That's an Egyptian god
Anubis on the left,

00:05:36.610 --> 00:05:40.270 align:middle line:84%
sitting on the right
on his holy ark.

00:05:40.270 --> 00:05:44.170 align:middle line:84%
Egyptian Ark Anubis
was pictured as a dog

00:05:44.170 --> 00:05:49.060 align:middle line:84%
because it represents the star
system of Sirius, the dog star.

00:05:49.060 --> 00:05:52.240 align:middle line:10%
And so Sirius the
dog star, in order

00:05:52.240 --> 00:05:58.480 align:middle line:10%
to honor the god in Sirius,
they made it into a dog,

00:05:58.480 --> 00:06:02.260 align:middle line:10%
so because Sirius is
referred to as the dog star.

00:06:02.260 --> 00:06:04.430 align:middle line:84%
But the point is, on
the right-hand side,

00:06:04.430 --> 00:06:08.800 align:middle line:84%
you will see the dog
star sitting on the Holy

00:06:08.800 --> 00:06:12.190 align:middle line:90%
Ark of the Covenant in Egypt.

00:06:12.190 --> 00:06:15.280 align:middle line:10%
And here's that same Ark
when it was originally

00:06:15.280 --> 00:06:18.850 align:middle line:10%
found by Lord Carnarvon in
Egypt many, many years ago.

00:06:18.850 --> 00:06:22.000 align:middle line:90%


00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:23.710 align:middle line:84%
If you'll remember,
in the movie,

00:06:23.710 --> 00:06:30.110 align:middle line:84%
Indiana Jones has to find the
Lost Ark in a tomb in Egypt.

00:06:30.110 --> 00:06:32.380 align:middle line:10%
The very word, the
lower paragraph

00:06:32.380 --> 00:06:35.350 align:middle line:10%
says the very idea of
the Ark of the Covenant

00:06:35.350 --> 00:06:37.630 align:middle line:10%
was copied from the Egyptians.

00:06:37.630 --> 00:06:41.320 align:middle line:10%
So this is what you'll find
in most all reference works.

00:06:41.320 --> 00:06:43.810 align:middle line:84%
It will tell you, even in
Bible dictionaries will

00:06:43.810 --> 00:06:47.740 align:middle line:84%
tell you there was no Ark
of the Covenant in Israel,

00:06:47.740 --> 00:06:52.110 align:middle line:84%
but there was an original
Ark of the Contract in Egypt.

00:06:52.110 --> 00:06:53.960 align:middle line:10%
So here we see on
the left-hand side

00:06:53.960 --> 00:06:57.560 align:middle line:10%
the Egyptians carrying their
holy Ark, and on the right side

00:06:57.560 --> 00:07:03.930 align:middle line:10%
the Hebrews carrying the Ark
which was the borrowed story.

00:07:03.930 --> 00:07:07.040 align:middle line:10%
And so the original Ark
and the mythical Ark.

00:07:07.040 --> 00:07:09.830 align:middle line:10%
This is very important
to keep in mind,

00:07:09.830 --> 00:07:12.260 align:middle line:10%
because when you look at the
Lost Ark of the Covenant,

00:07:12.260 --> 00:07:15.710 align:middle line:10%
it supposedly is a very
important symbol to the Hebrew

00:07:15.710 --> 00:07:18.680 align:middle line:10%
religion, but now
we're finding out

00:07:18.680 --> 00:07:21.590 align:middle line:10%
that it's actually an
Egyptian symbol, had nothing

00:07:21.590 --> 00:07:23.450 align:middle line:10%
to do with the ancient Hebrews.

00:07:23.450 --> 00:07:27.560 align:middle line:84%
Even National Geographics
did a piece on,

00:07:27.560 --> 00:07:31.040 align:middle line:84%
a video show on the
Ark of the Covenant,

00:07:31.040 --> 00:07:35.540 align:middle line:84%
and which they entitled it
"Many Legends But No Evidence."

00:07:35.540 --> 00:07:40.590 align:middle line:10%
The idea of having a
holy chest or a holy ark

00:07:40.590 --> 00:07:42.770 align:middle line:10%
is an Egyptian idea.

00:07:42.770 --> 00:07:44.570 align:middle line:10%
It's an Egyptian concept.

00:07:44.570 --> 00:07:46.400 align:middle line:10%
The point being is
that it would have

00:07:46.400 --> 00:07:49.790 align:middle line:10%
been a copy of an Egyptian ark.

00:07:49.790 --> 00:07:56.150 align:middle line:84%
And so today, incidentally, in
the Ethiopian Orthodox Church

00:07:56.150 --> 00:07:59.120 align:middle line:84%
in Ethiopia, they
claim to actually

00:07:59.120 --> 00:08:02.450 align:middle line:84%
have the original Ark of
the Covenant of the Hebrews

00:08:02.450 --> 00:08:04.400 align:middle line:90%
at that church.

00:08:04.400 --> 00:08:07.190 align:middle line:84%
But they go on to say that
the object is currently

00:08:07.190 --> 00:08:11.900 align:middle line:84%
kept under strict guard in
the treasury of the church.

00:08:11.900 --> 00:08:13.790 align:middle line:10%
And so you can't
come in to see it.

00:08:13.790 --> 00:08:15.200 align:middle line:84%
But they've got
it, but you can't

00:08:15.200 --> 00:08:19.310 align:middle line:84%
see it, which is, of course,
convenient because you don't

00:08:19.310 --> 00:08:20.700 align:middle line:90%
know if they have it or not.

00:08:20.700 --> 00:08:24.140 align:middle line:84%
If they have it, you
can't see it anyway.

00:08:24.140 --> 00:08:26.840 align:middle line:84%
There are many mysteries
surrounding the Ark,

00:08:26.840 --> 00:08:30.980 align:middle line:84%
many questions about what
is it and where is it

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:33.980 align:middle line:90%
and who actually owns it.

00:08:33.980 --> 00:08:39.260 align:middle line:84%
But I don't believe that the Ark
of the Covenant ever existed.

00:08:39.260 --> 00:08:42.200 align:middle line:84%
From my understanding,
it never existed.

00:08:42.200 --> 00:08:46.100 align:middle line:84%
It was borrowed from day one,
the idea, from the Egyptians.

00:08:46.100 --> 00:08:49.940 align:middle line:10%
However, there are many other
mysteries and strange things

00:08:49.940 --> 00:08:53.840 align:middle line:10%
in relation to the Ark,
and the Holy Bible,

00:08:53.840 --> 00:08:57.410 align:middle line:10%
in the New Testament, the
last book of the Bible

00:08:57.410 --> 00:08:59.680 align:middle line:10%
is called the Book
of Revelation.

00:08:59.680 --> 00:09:01.940 align:middle line:10%
And in the Book
of Revelation, it

00:09:01.940 --> 00:09:06.110 align:middle line:10%
tells you why no one
has and no one ever

00:09:06.110 --> 00:09:08.930 align:middle line:10%
will find the Lost Ark.

00:09:08.930 --> 00:09:13.820 align:middle line:84%
And it says, "the temple of
God was opened in heaven,

00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:16.550 align:middle line:84%
and there was seen the
Ark of the Covenant,

00:09:16.550 --> 00:09:18.275 align:middle line:90%
the Ark of the Testament."

00:09:18.275 --> 00:09:24.460 align:middle line:90%


00:09:24.460 --> 00:09:26.620 align:middle line:84%
Right, now the next
subject I would

00:09:26.620 --> 00:09:31.000 align:middle line:84%
like to share with you is about
the King Solomon in the Bible.

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:35.050 align:middle line:84%
A very important name in the
biblical history of the Hebrews

00:09:35.050 --> 00:09:36.970 align:middle line:90%
was King Solomon.

00:09:36.970 --> 00:09:41.320 align:middle line:84%
And incidentally, the Temple
Institute in Jerusalem today

00:09:41.320 --> 00:09:44.290 align:middle line:84%
is preparing-- they've
already spent $27 million,

00:09:44.290 --> 00:09:48.190 align:middle line:84%
we're told, on
preparing a building

00:09:48.190 --> 00:09:51.520 align:middle line:84%
for the rebuilding of the
Jewish temple, the old temple

00:09:51.520 --> 00:09:53.740 align:middle line:90%
of Solomon.

00:09:53.740 --> 00:09:56.650 align:middle line:84%
The first thing we need to
know about the ancient temple

00:09:56.650 --> 00:09:59.440 align:middle line:84%
of King Solomon is that
there was no ancient King

00:09:59.440 --> 00:10:04.180 align:middle line:84%
Solomon to start with, and he
didn't have a temple, either.

00:10:04.180 --> 00:10:05.950 align:middle line:10%
There are some reference
works out there

00:10:05.950 --> 00:10:09.640 align:middle line:10%
about the temple showing
that it was just a story,

00:10:09.640 --> 00:10:11.080 align:middle line:10%
and that there was no temple.

00:10:11.080 --> 00:10:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And today, there are a lot of
academic books being written

00:10:15.640 --> 00:10:18.400 align:middle line:84%
about the whole
idea of King Solomon

00:10:18.400 --> 00:10:23.290 align:middle line:84%
as a king is a myth, a
king that never existed.

00:10:23.290 --> 00:10:27.040 align:middle line:84%
And so here's one article
called "The Myth of Solomon."

00:10:27.040 --> 00:10:29.980 align:middle line:84%
This is written by the
Department of Classical

00:10:29.980 --> 00:10:33.820 align:middle line:84%
and Near Eastern Studies
in Melbourne, Australia.

00:10:33.820 --> 00:10:36.160 align:middle line:10%
Another book, called
"The Templars,

00:10:36.160 --> 00:10:40.990 align:middle line:10%
or the History of the Myth
from Solomon's Temple."

00:10:40.990 --> 00:10:44.950 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, Solomon became
king because his father

00:10:44.950 --> 00:10:46.840 align:middle line:90%
was King David.

00:10:46.840 --> 00:10:50.410 align:middle line:84%
So when his father
left the kingship,

00:10:50.410 --> 00:10:53.230 align:middle line:84%
it was given to King
Solomon, his son.

00:10:53.230 --> 00:10:57.040 align:middle line:84%
So King Solomon was
very famous in history

00:10:57.040 --> 00:11:01.070 align:middle line:84%
for being a very
wise man, and very,

00:11:01.070 --> 00:11:05.770 align:middle line:84%
very highly intelligent
and very interesting.

00:11:05.770 --> 00:11:09.970 align:middle line:84%
He was a very wise
man, wise King Solomon.

00:11:09.970 --> 00:11:12.000 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, well we're
told that he built

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:17.020 align:middle line:84%
a whole nation,
and great temples

00:11:17.020 --> 00:11:19.690 align:middle line:84%
and all kinds of
marvelous things

00:11:19.690 --> 00:11:23.480 align:middle line:84%
that this King Solomon
did for the Jewish people.

00:11:23.480 --> 00:11:27.100 align:middle line:10%
But in point of fact, today,
reference works coming out

00:11:27.100 --> 00:11:30.670 align:middle line:10%
of Israel say that there is no
evidence that King Solomon ever

00:11:30.670 --> 00:11:33.140 align:middle line:10%
lived, and for sure
there's no evidence

00:11:33.140 --> 00:11:37.630 align:middle line:10%
a great civilisation or
temples or anything at all

00:11:37.630 --> 00:11:39.580 align:middle line:10%
was ever erected
to King Solomon.

00:11:39.580 --> 00:11:41.680 align:middle line:10%
They've never heard of it.

00:11:41.680 --> 00:11:46.110 align:middle line:84%
Donald Redford, an author and
leading authority on the era,

00:11:46.110 --> 00:11:49.570 align:middle line:84%
writes in frustration about
the absence of anything

00:11:49.570 --> 00:11:54.310 align:middle line:84%
to verify or to prove
the Bible stories.

00:11:54.310 --> 00:11:59.140 align:middle line:84%
