had two phallic symbols holding

00:25:24.790 --> 00:25:26.820 align:middle line:10%
up the canopy of heaven.

00:25:26.820 --> 00:25:30.800 align:middle line:10%
The two phallic symbols are
the two phallic pillars.

00:25:30.800 --> 00:25:33.640 align:middle line:84%
It's a very important
symbolism in ancient Egypt,

00:25:33.640 --> 00:25:36.130 align:middle line:84%
and it's found
quite a few places.

00:25:36.130 --> 00:25:41.440 align:middle line:10%
The twin towers
idea, worldwide, in

00:25:41.440 --> 00:25:43.990 align:middle line:10%
the old ancient
Babylonian system,

00:25:43.990 --> 00:25:46.150 align:middle line:10%
the kings that would
rise in the morning

00:25:46.150 --> 00:25:49.960 align:middle line:10%
between twin towers,
two towers, this

00:25:49.960 --> 00:25:52.210 align:middle line:10%
is the old Babylonian system.

00:25:52.210 --> 00:25:54.190 align:middle line:84%
In India, you have
the gods standing

00:25:54.190 --> 00:25:57.080 align:middle line:90%
between the two towers.

00:25:57.080 --> 00:25:59.490 align:middle line:90%
It was an idea of twin columns.

00:25:59.490 --> 00:26:02.470 align:middle line:10%
It goes back into
the ancient world.

00:26:02.470 --> 00:26:05.920 align:middle line:84%
The twin towers are
connected to the concept

00:26:05.920 --> 00:26:09.490 align:middle line:84%
in the ancient world of
twin phallic pillars.

00:26:09.490 --> 00:26:11.500 align:middle line:84%
Here we have the
twin, the pillars

00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:15.940 align:middle line:84%
on each side of the opening
and then the large twin pillars

00:26:15.940 --> 00:26:18.690 align:middle line:90%
on both sides.

00:26:18.690 --> 00:26:22.830 align:middle line:84%
The idea comes from
a biblical story

00:26:22.830 --> 00:26:27.330 align:middle line:84%
about a symbol which today has
been taken up by Freemasonry.

00:26:27.330 --> 00:26:31.140 align:middle line:10%
The Masonic Order has
taken from the Bible

00:26:31.140 --> 00:26:34.770 align:middle line:10%
the story about Jachin and Boaz.

00:26:34.770 --> 00:26:38.580 align:middle line:10%
They were twin towers, or
they were twin pillars.

00:26:38.580 --> 00:26:43.010 align:middle line:84%
And they represented
two phallic pillars.

00:26:43.010 --> 00:26:46.221 align:middle line:84%
And so we're talking
about phallic worship now.

00:26:46.221 --> 00:26:47.970 align:middle line:84%
And this is something
that a lot of people

00:26:47.970 --> 00:26:50.880 align:middle line:84%
don't connect to the
idea of twin towers.

00:26:50.880 --> 00:26:55.110 align:middle line:84%
But it goes back into an
ancient time where the idea was

00:26:55.110 --> 00:26:57.930 align:middle line:90%
two phallic pillars.

00:26:57.930 --> 00:27:00.435 align:middle line:10%
And they were called Jachin
and Boaz in the Bible.

00:27:00.435 --> 00:27:03.225 align:middle line:10%
And this is a
Masonic symbol today.

00:27:03.225 --> 00:27:05.790 align:middle line:10%
It has been picked up
and used in Freemasonry

00:27:05.790 --> 00:27:08.470 align:middle line:10%
around the world.

00:27:08.470 --> 00:27:10.590 align:middle line:84%
The reason why is
because you need

00:27:10.590 --> 00:27:12.540 align:middle line:90%
the two to hold up the heavens.

00:27:12.540 --> 00:27:14.250 align:middle line:90%
You can't do it with one.

00:27:14.250 --> 00:27:17.400 align:middle line:10%
And so the ancient
Egyptians always

00:27:17.400 --> 00:27:19.935 align:middle line:10%
showed two towers,
or two pillars.

00:27:19.935 --> 00:27:23.380 align:middle line:90%


00:27:23.380 --> 00:27:27.670 align:middle line:10%
There is obviously more yet,
to the story of twin towers,

00:27:27.670 --> 00:27:29.980 align:middle line:10%
but I'm just giving you
a brief introduction

00:27:29.980 --> 00:27:35.320 align:middle line:10%
to the idea that there is
a symbolism involved here

00:27:35.320 --> 00:27:38.260 align:middle line:10%
that most people are
not aware of until you

00:27:38.260 --> 00:27:42.910 align:middle line:10%
begin to see how many times
that idea keeps popping up.

00:27:42.910 --> 00:27:47.310 align:middle line:90%


00:27:47.310 --> 00:27:51.000 align:middle line:10%
A lot of people, when you
mention the word New Age,

00:27:51.000 --> 00:27:55.980 align:middle line:10%
it causes visions of people
who are into metaphysics,

00:27:55.980 --> 00:28:00.360 align:middle line:10%
spiritual retreats,
hallucinogenics,

00:28:00.360 --> 00:28:05.460 align:middle line:10%
all sorts of ideas are
generated by the term New Age.

00:28:05.460 --> 00:28:08.760 align:middle line:84%
And it has become a very
important subject, especially

00:28:08.760 --> 00:28:10.620 align:middle line:90%
in the religious world.

00:28:10.620 --> 00:28:15.990 align:middle line:84%
Are we humans on this Earth
approaching a New Age which

00:28:15.990 --> 00:28:18.440 align:middle line:84%
is filled with darkness
and evil because this

00:28:18.440 --> 00:28:22.530 align:middle line:84%
is what Christianity is
portraying the New Age as?

00:28:22.530 --> 00:28:25.670 align:middle line:84%
I want to show you
that that is incorrect.

00:28:25.670 --> 00:28:28.590 align:middle line:84%
That the New Age is in
the Bible all the way

00:28:28.590 --> 00:28:32.190 align:middle line:84%
through the scriptures it
talks about the New Age.

00:28:32.190 --> 00:28:36.940 align:middle line:84%
Everyone has heard the stories
of the end of the world.

00:28:36.940 --> 00:28:38.970 align:middle line:84%
And there's a lot of
talk about the New

00:28:38.970 --> 00:28:41.740 align:middle line:90%
Age as the end of the world.

00:28:41.740 --> 00:28:46.770 align:middle line:84%
But very few people realize that
both subjects about the New Age

00:28:46.770 --> 00:28:49.380 align:middle line:84%
and the end of the world
are the same thing.

00:28:49.380 --> 00:28:53.160 align:middle line:90%


00:28:53.160 --> 00:28:55.460 align:middle line:84%
Let's start with the
end of the world.

00:28:55.460 --> 00:28:59.690 align:middle line:84%
And then we'll go to the
origins of the New Age,

00:28:59.690 --> 00:29:03.480 align:middle line:84%
and then the Christian
church's view.

00:29:03.480 --> 00:29:06.290 align:middle line:10%
First of all, we've been
hearing about this idea

00:29:06.290 --> 00:29:09.080 align:middle line:10%
of the end of the
world for hundreds

00:29:09.080 --> 00:29:10.840 align:middle line:10%
if not thousands of years.

00:29:10.840 --> 00:29:13.100 align:middle line:84%
There have been religions
around the world talking

00:29:13.100 --> 00:29:16.910 align:middle line:84%
about the end of the
world, and especially

00:29:16.910 --> 00:29:18.770 align:middle line:90%
nowadays with the world today.

00:29:18.770 --> 00:29:24.320 align:middle line:84%
The end of the world which
implies a world conflagration

00:29:24.320 --> 00:29:28.960 align:middle line:84%
of wars and violence,
atomic destruction,

00:29:28.960 --> 00:29:32.260 align:middle line:84%
chaotic destruction
of the human race,

00:29:32.260 --> 00:29:38.050 align:middle line:84%
famines, disease, wars,
violence, revolutions.

00:29:38.050 --> 00:29:41.110 align:middle line:10%
The entire idea of
the end of the world

00:29:41.110 --> 00:29:46.420 align:middle line:10%
is apocalyptic in proportions
implying the end of humanity

00:29:46.420 --> 00:29:47.860 align:middle line:10%
itself.

00:29:47.860 --> 00:29:51.310 align:middle line:84%
Let's see what the actual
term end of the world

00:29:51.310 --> 00:29:55.750 align:middle line:84%
really means from the
Bible's viewpoint.

00:29:55.750 --> 00:29:58.920 align:middle line:10%
We have books called "The
End of the World," "How Will

00:29:58.920 --> 00:30:03.880 align:middle line:10%
the World End," "The Atomic
Bomb and the End of the World."

00:30:03.880 --> 00:30:06.070 align:middle line:10%
The New Testament
King James version

00:30:06.070 --> 00:30:10.050 align:middle line:10%
talks about in the
book of Matthew, 13,

00:30:10.050 --> 00:30:12.850 align:middle line:10%
it says that Jesus
said the enemy that

00:30:12.850 --> 00:30:15.490 align:middle line:10%
sows them is the
devil, and the harvest

00:30:15.490 --> 00:30:17.140 align:middle line:10%
is the end of the world.

00:30:17.140 --> 00:30:21.160 align:middle line:84%
Here's Jesus talking about
the end of the world.

00:30:21.160 --> 00:30:24.070 align:middle line:84%
End of the world,
but important is

00:30:24.070 --> 00:30:29.290 align:middle line:84%
what does the word world mean
and where does it come from?

00:30:29.290 --> 00:30:31.750 align:middle line:84%
Interesting also is
another scripture

00:30:31.750 --> 00:30:33.880 align:middle line:84%
in the Bible, Jesus
talks about something

00:30:33.880 --> 00:30:37.510 align:middle line:90%
he called the regeneration.

00:30:37.510 --> 00:30:40.600 align:middle line:10%
The footnote says it
will mean a renewal

00:30:40.600 --> 00:30:44.950 align:middle line:10%
or a recreation of the
whole social order on Earth.

00:30:44.950 --> 00:30:48.250 align:middle line:10%
Jesus talked about
this regeneration.

00:30:48.250 --> 00:30:51.010 align:middle line:10%
And then adds that
that regeneration

00:30:51.010 --> 00:30:53.410 align:middle line:10%
will be God's kingdom.

00:30:53.410 --> 00:30:55.870 align:middle line:84%
Here we have in the
scriptures talking

00:30:55.870 --> 00:30:58.360 align:middle line:84%
about what Jesus said,
"Verily I say unto

00:30:58.360 --> 00:31:02.870 align:middle line:84%
you, you who follow me in the
regeneration of the world."

00:31:02.870 --> 00:31:05.920 align:middle line:84%
We've seen regeneration
means making it new,

00:31:05.920 --> 00:31:08.830 align:middle line:90%
recreating the whole world.

00:31:08.830 --> 00:31:11.170 align:middle line:84%
And we find other
Bible translations

00:31:11.170 --> 00:31:14.590 align:middle line:84%
when speaking about this
recreation of the social order

00:31:14.590 --> 00:31:20.790 align:middle line:84%
of the world refers to it as the
New World Order, the new world.

00:31:20.790 --> 00:31:23.200 align:middle line:84%
In "The Interpreter's
Bible Dictionary,"

00:31:23.200 --> 00:31:26.380 align:middle line:84%
we see it talking
about the regeneration.

00:31:26.380 --> 00:31:28.840 align:middle line:84%
And it says that this
regeneration, there

00:31:28.840 --> 00:31:33.640 align:middle line:84%
is a reward in the world to
come, which is a regeneration,

00:31:33.640 --> 00:31:35.740 align:middle line:90%
or a new world.

00:31:35.740 --> 00:31:37.880 align:middle line:84%
So that does not
imply that there's

00:31:37.880 --> 00:31:41.080 align:middle line:84%
a destruction of the whole
humanity in the world when

00:31:41.080 --> 00:31:45.430 align:middle line:84%
there's going to be a reward
and a time of regeneration,

00:31:45.430 --> 00:31:46.990 align:middle line:90%
or the new world.

00:31:46.990 --> 00:31:51.250 align:middle line:84%
"The Commentary Bible"
says, the promise

00:31:51.250 --> 00:31:55.930 align:middle line:84%
has to do with the new world,
a regeneration or a rebirth

00:31:55.930 --> 00:32:00.700 align:middle line:84%
in an age to come, there will be
a new heavens and a new earth.

00:32:00.700 --> 00:32:03.820 align:middle line:84%
Here in the "Bible
Encyclopedia" it says,

00:32:03.820 --> 00:32:07.270 align:middle line:84%
in the new world or
the regeneration.

00:32:07.270 --> 00:32:09.580 align:middle line:84%
Again, that word
keeps coming up.

00:32:09.580 --> 00:32:11.830 align:middle line:84%
Josephus used it
as the restoration

00:32:11.830 --> 00:32:13.720 align:middle line:90%
of the land of Israel.

00:32:13.720 --> 00:32:17.440 align:middle line:84%
Jewish hopes await a
renewal both of the land

00:32:17.440 --> 00:32:19.640 align:middle line:90%
and the entire world.

00:32:19.640 --> 00:32:23.530 align:middle line:84%
And so the Son of Man,
Jesus, his domination

00:32:23.530 --> 00:32:27.700 align:middle line:84%
will be in the time, which
is called the new age.

00:32:27.700 --> 00:32:31.150 align:middle line:84%
So in the New
Testament word, world,

00:32:31.150 --> 00:32:33.850 align:middle line:90%
is actually a Greek word, aion.

00:32:33.850 --> 00:32:36.010 align:middle line:90%
Aion does not mean world.

00:32:36.010 --> 00:32:39.490 align:middle line:84%
It was a mistranslation
and a misunderstanding

00:32:39.490 --> 00:32:43.930 align:middle line:84%
by the church fathers who
translated the Latin Vulgate.

00:32:43.930 --> 00:32:46.900 align:middle line:84%
They took the word
from the Greek, aion,

00:32:46.900 --> 00:32:49.390 align:middle line:90%
and thought it meant world.

00:32:49.390 --> 00:32:52.640 align:middle line:84%
Well, now we understand,
no, it was a mistake.

00:32:52.640 --> 00:32:54.810 align:middle line:90%
World is age.

00:32:54.810 --> 00:32:59.320 align:middle line:90%
The word age is actually aion.

00:32:59.320 --> 00:33:04.700 align:middle line:84%
So when you hear people talking
about the end of the world,

00:33:04.700 --> 00:33:08.110 align:middle line:84%
no, it's the end of
an age which implies

00:33:08.110 --> 00:33:10.590 align:middle line:90%
that there's a new age coming.

00:33:10.590 --> 00:33:13.390 align:middle line:84%
And there has been
other ages in the past,

00:33:13.390 --> 00:33:15.790 align:middle line:84%
and we're living in
a particular age now.

00:33:15.790 --> 00:33:19.150 align:middle line:10%
And there will be
a new age coming.

00:33:19.150 --> 00:33:22.210 align:middle line:10%
For instance, here's a
quote from a reference

00:33:22.210 --> 00:33:23.620 align:middle line:10%
work on the Bible.

00:33:23.620 --> 00:33:27.610 align:middle line:10%
It says, "The world,
or age to come,

00:33:27.610 --> 00:33:31.060 align:middle line:10%
was a familiar expression among
the Jews for the Messiah's

00:33:31.060 --> 00:33:32.940 align:middle line:10%
Kingdom.

00:33:32.940 --> 00:33:36.550 align:middle line:10%
And in the New Testament it's
employed partly in regard

00:33:36.550 --> 00:33:38.920 align:middle line:10%
to the kingdom as
now established

00:33:38.920 --> 00:33:42.220 align:middle line:10%
and partly in regard to
the future development,

00:33:42.220 --> 00:33:44.020 align:middle line:10%
the age of glory.

00:33:44.020 --> 00:33:48.160 align:middle line:84%
It is used in this
later sense by our Lord.

00:33:48.160 --> 00:33:50.710 align:middle line:84%
And the ages of the
world are therefore

00:33:50.710 --> 00:33:55.000 align:middle line:84%
the great cycles of
time, they are great ages

00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:59.020 align:middle line:84%
where the degeneracy and
corruption are the progression

00:33:59.020 --> 00:34:01.480 align:middle line:84%
and development through
which it has always

00:34:01.480 --> 00:34:05.560 align:middle line:84%
been destined to pass, and
in part has passed already."

00:34:05.560 --> 00:34:09.159 align:middle line:84%
So what we're talking
about in a New Age

00:34:09.159 --> 00:34:12.550 align:middle line:84%
is the ages of time
which have come and gone.

00:34:12.550 --> 00:34:15.710 align:middle line:84%
Civilizations are
founded and grow,

00:34:15.710 --> 00:34:19.510 align:middle line:84%
and then they die and
new civilizations come.

00:34:19.510 --> 00:34:23.889 align:middle line:84%
And so the whole idea of aion
is a continual progression

00:34:23.889 --> 00:34:27.100 align:middle line:90%
of the ages of the world.

00:34:27.100 --> 00:34:32.010 align:middle line:10%
Here in John 9:32
it says sometimes

00:34:32.010 --> 00:34:35.040 align:middle line:10%
the world, and
especially this world,

00:34:35.040 --> 00:34:39.179 align:middle line:10%
seems to denote where
else in the New Testament

00:34:39.179 --> 00:34:43.620 align:middle line:10%
is called the present
age, or world.

00:34:43.620 --> 00:34:46.480 align:middle line:84%
The "New Oxford Dictionary
with the Apocrypha,"

00:34:46.480 --> 00:34:50.610 align:middle line:84%
it says at the top,
Jesus said, "I say to you

00:34:50.610 --> 00:34:53.350 align:middle line:84%
that in the new
world--" so here Jesus

00:34:53.350 --> 00:34:55.139 align:middle line:90%
is talking about the new world.

00:34:55.139 --> 00:34:57.390 align:middle line:90%
No, new age.

00:34:57.390 --> 00:34:59.880 align:middle line:84%
"The Interpreters
Bible Dictionary,"

00:34:59.880 --> 00:35:03.000 align:middle line:84%
it says consummation
is fittingly

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:05.190 align:middle line:90%
celebrated by a new song.

00:35:05.190 --> 00:35:09.240 align:middle line:84%
When the return from
exile heralds a new age.

00:35:09.240 --> 00:35:11.250 align:middle line:90%
Now we're getting it right.

00:35:11.250 --> 00:35:15.300 align:middle line:10%
So that it goes on to say,
the New Testament ideas

00:35:15.300 --> 00:35:19.260 align:middle line:10%
are taken up and applied to
the Kingdom of God introduced

00:35:19.260 --> 00:35:23.430 align:middle line:10%
by Christ, his hearers
recognized in his ministry

00:35:23.430 --> 00:35:29.700 align:middle line:10%
a new teaching, a new age
which draws with his ministry,

00:35:29.700 --> 00:35:36.930 align:middle line:10%
is a regeneration, or a
new world, but is new age.

00:35:36.930 --> 00:35:40.380 align:middle line:10%
Here in Matthew we see
the "Harper Study Bible

00:35:40.380 --> 00:35:45.330 align:middle line:10%
Dictionary," it says where
Jesus said to his apostles,

00:35:45.330 --> 00:35:48.940 align:middle line:10%
"Truly I say to you
in the new world."

00:35:48.940 --> 00:35:52.440 align:middle line:84%
Again, a misunderstanding
of the word aion.

00:35:52.440 --> 00:35:55.500 align:middle line:90%
It's the new age.

00:35:55.500 --> 00:35:57.390 align:middle line:84%
"Expository Dictionary
of the Bible"

00:35:57.390 --> 00:36:00.990 align:middle line:84%
says, the Greek words,
various Greek words

00:36:00.990 --> 00:36:06.570 align:middle line:84%
are translated world
in the Bible, age, aion

00:36:06.570 --> 00:36:11.470 align:middle line:84%
which means age and
translated world.

00:36:11.470 --> 00:36:13.890 align:middle line:84%
So here is a classic
example, just showing

00:36:13.890 --> 00:36:17.600 align:middle line:84%
you very simply that the
translators of the Bible

00:36:17.600 --> 00:36:20.820 align:middle line:90%
misunderstood the Greek word.

00:36:20.820 --> 00:36:24.660 align:middle line:84%
Now we will see that many
modern Bible translations are

00:36:24.660 --> 00:36:28.620 align:middle line:84%
correct when they are
translating the word aion, not

00:36:28.620 --> 00:36:32.910 align:middle line:90%
as world but as an age.

00:36:32.910 --> 00:36:36.870 align:middle line:84%
Here we have, for instance,
Jesus said, I will be with you.

00:36:36.870 --> 00:36:39.130 align:middle line:84%
He's talking about
his apostles, and he

00:36:39.130 --> 00:36:45.210 align:middle line:84%
said, I will be with you even to
the end of the age, not world,

00:36:45.210 --> 00:36:47.400 align:middle line:90%
end of the age.

00:36:47.400 --> 00:36:49.650 align:middle line:10%
The Holy Bible, new
and old translations,

00:36:49.650 --> 00:36:53.850 align:middle line:10%
we see marks clear
distinction between the reward

00:36:53.850 --> 00:37:00.060 align:middle line:10%
already in this age and the
reward in the age to come,

00:37:00.060 --> 00:37:04.380 align:middle line:10%
showing those two ages, the
old age and the new age.

00:37:04.380 --> 00:37:08.460 align:middle line:84%
And it says in the Bible,
in the age to come.

00:37:08.460 --> 00:37:14.070 align:middle line:84%
The New Testament says,
and this is Ephesians 2,

00:37:14.070 --> 00:37:16.590 align:middle line:90%
it says, in the ages to come.

00:37:16.590 --> 00:37:18.610 align:middle line:90%
This is a new translation.

00:37:18.610 --> 00:37:19.980 align:middle line:90%
And now they're doing it right.

00:37:19.980 --> 00:37:24.030 align:middle line:84%
Now they're saying
that aion means age.

00:37:24.030 --> 00:37:27.600 align:middle line:84%
Ephesians says, in
the ages to come.

00:37:27.600 --> 00:37:31.530 align:middle line:10%
We even have Jesus himself
promising that his kingdom will

00:37:31.530 --> 00:37:34.930 align:middle line:10%
be coming in the new age.

00:37:34.930 --> 00:37:38.590 align:middle line:10%
Jesus replied, it
says in the scripture,

00:37:38.590 --> 00:37:44.700 align:middle line:10%
Jesus replied, truly I tell
you in the world that is to be,

00:37:44.700 --> 00:37:48.750 align:middle line:10%
again, the new concise
Bible translation says,

